{"lemma":"كَنْسُ","slug":"كَنْسُ","root":"ك.ن.س","root_slug":"ك-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَنْسُ","root":"كنس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37299"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hide, to retreat","examples":[{"text":"أُقْسِمُ بِالْخُنَّسِ الْجَوَارِ الْكُنَّسِ","english":"I swear by the receding [planets], which fly by and fade"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sweep","examples":[{"text":"أطفأتُ المكيّف وفتحت النافذة، فدخل الهواء البحريّ حارّاً وكنس الأوكسجين المُعلّب غير الصحّي من قفصي الصدري.","english":"I quenched the air conditioner and opened the window, and sea wind entered hot and swept the unhealthy canned oxygen out of my ribcage."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plural of كَانِس (kānis, active participle of كَنَسَ (kanasa))","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ك ن س (k n s). In Fraenkel’s and Nöldeke’s view the meaning “to sweep” is from Aramaic כְּנַשׁ / ܟܢܫ (kənaš, “to gather; to sweep”), denominal via مِكْنَسَة (miknasa, “broom”). Note Mehri kənūs (“to sweep”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37299","headword_ar":"كَنَسَ","root":"kns","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanosN","text_ar":"كَنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swept"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA) a house, or chamber, (S, A, Mgh, Msb,) or place, (TA,) with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mikonasap","text_ar":"مِكْنَسَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or broom]. (A, Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~uwA bihimo fakanasuwhumo","text_ar":"مَرُّوا بِهِمْ فَكَنَسُوهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They passed by them and swept them away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaHuwhumo","text_ar":"كَسَحُوهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanasa","text_ar":"كَنَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunuwsN","text_ar":"كُنُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an antelope)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kinaAs","text_ar":"كِنَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) i. e., his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hiding-place, among trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkn~s","text_ar":"تكنّس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktns","text_ar":"اكتنس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";) (A, TA;) which two verbs are likewise said of a wild bull or cow, in the same sense. (TA.) [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkn~s","text_ar":"تكنّس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered the tent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hid himself, and entered the tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkn~st","text_ar":"تكنّست","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawodaj","text_ar":"هَوْدَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel-litter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) app. taken from the saying of Lebeed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatakan~asuwA quTonFA","text_ar":"فَتَكَنَّسُوا قُطْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they entered"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawaAdij","text_ar":"هَوَادِج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel-litters"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covered with cloths of cotton."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanasati Aln~ujuwmu","text_ar":"كَنَسَتِ النُّجُومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (AO, Zj, S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunuwsN","text_ar":"كُنُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Zj,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars hid themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"in their place, or places, of setting, (AO, Zj, S, K, *) like antelopes in their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunus","text_ar":"كُنُس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or coverts]: (K:) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued in their courses and then departed, returning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"planets"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became stationary in their circuiting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revolving."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnisN","text_ar":"كَانِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","TA","K","Zj","AO","Lth"]}]}}